<subSubSection id="098CF4F5AD8A930F372153C7C80B7C68" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" type="notes">
<paragraph id="D2F6AC37F29B7BA252653F37A8A49FB9" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B431E0F857183F75D76267AFC586BF2C" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
First record for Bulgaria. 
<emphasis id="7A950755EFEA575FBB725F6672235404" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Western Danube Plain</emphasis>
: Guljantsi vill., 07.viii.2021, 2♂♂ and 2♀♀ (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C9D5641D78229CA636C9E0AC94ED1E9D" captionStartId="F7727335" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">1</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis id="497D7EA18568D2929DF6F965860197AB" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Western Rhodopes Mts.</emphasis>
:, Djadovci vill., 26.v.2014, 9♂♂ and 4♀♀; Bachkovo vill., 29.v.2021, 1♂; 
<emphasis id="DEC01EE3C2D86F291E2C30B67C4CD565" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Eastern Rhodopes Mts.</emphasis>
: Zimzelen vill., 25.v.2014, 3♂♂ and 1♀; Bjal Gradec vill., 02.vi.2015, 2♂♂ and 1 nymph; Dolno Lukovo vill., 01.vi.2015, 1♂. All specimens were collected on 
<taxonomicName id="AB3BE1A4D9AB3F973EA73E29503FC8FD" class="Insecta" family="Delphacidae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salix" order="Hemiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="71D21FD7A517FF30552077B61E71BEB9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Salix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shrubs. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="77E4A5BCB08A177444DA5DD08E5CC018" author="Gjonov, I." journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Upper Silesian Museum in Bytom. Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" refId="B7727581" refString="Gjonov, I., 2022. new_fulgoromorpha_records_bulgaria_2022. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="new _ fulgoromorpha _ records _ bulgaria _ 2022" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Gjonov (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0D23805FEE48A1321DBF700058CEC939" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
This species is recorded as a pest in the Caucasus (
<bibRefCitation id="74865FB7ECCC68AF6BEF32422D9849F2" author="Emeljanov, Alexandr Fedorovich" journalOrPublisher="Key to the fauna of Russia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" pagination="1 - 252" refId="B7712483" refString="Emeljanov, Alexandr Fedorovich, 2015. Planthoppers of the family Cixiidae of Russia and adjacent territories. Key to the fauna of Russia 177: 1 - 252" title="Planthoppers of the family Cixiidae of Russia and adjacent territories" volume="177" year="2015">Emeljanov 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and Iran (
<bibRefCitation id="D720BBAD760ACA76F6102E2598E5F86E" author="Mozaffarian, Fariba" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Field Crop Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" pagination="1 - 16" refId="B7713239" refString="Mozaffarian, Fariba, 2014. Fauna of planthoppers superfamily Fulgoroidea (Hem.: Auchenorrhyncha) in the northwestern Iran. Journal of Field Crop Entomology 4 (1): 1 - 16" title="Fauna of planthoppers superfamily Fulgoroidea (Hem.: Auchenorrhyncha) in the northwestern Iran" volume="4" year="2014">Mozaffarian 2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C692F37D58D010C12D824971899B5783" author="Mozaffarian, Fariba" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" pagination="475 - 501" refId="B7712977" refString="Mozaffarian, Fariba, 2018. An Identification key to the species of Auchenorrhyncha of Iranian fauna recorded as pests in orchards and a review on the pest status of the species. Zootaxa 4420 (4): 475 - 501" title="An Identification key to the species of Auchenorrhyncha of Iranian fauna recorded as pests in orchards and a review on the pest status of the species" volume="4420" year="2018">Mozaffarian 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Although it is hardly a danger to crops in Bulgaria (being found only on willow bushes), it should be monitored in the future.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C8B7E37F01015F6B87C05A6459CEA52F" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
<emphasis id="5C26D385C052A876EB4F91910E08C796" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Red Lists</emphasis>
: No assessment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="813BD7F3DAEE5B8AFD8304BA89405127" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">
<emphasis id="D0A71413CA749156AFC2FE2E86BC66C4" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231">Host plant</emphasis>
: Polyphagous (
<bibRefCitation id="8DBCE858312E09AAE41CD47C66360D12" author="Emeljanov, Alexandr Fedorovich" journalOrPublisher="Key to the fauna of Russia" pageId="0" pageNumber="83231" pagination="1 - 252" refId="B7712483" refString="Emeljanov, Alexandr Fedorovich, 2015. Planthoppers of the family Cixiidae of Russia and adjacent territories. Key to the fauna of Russia 177: 1 - 252" title="Planthoppers of the family Cixiidae of Russia and adjacent territories" volume="177" year="2015">Emeljanov 2015</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
